SIMPLE: sullage
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sullage
<hw>Sul"lage</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Suillage</er>, <er>Sulliage</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Drainage
of filth; filth collected from the street or highway; sewage.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The streets were exceedingly large, well paved, having many vaults
and conveyances under them for <qex>sullage</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Evelyn.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which sullies or defiles.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is the privilege of the celestial luminaries to receive no
tincture, <qex>sullage</qex>, or difilement from the most noisome sinks
and dunghills here below.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Founding)</fld> <def>The scoria on the surface of
molten metal in the ladle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Hydraul. Engin.)</fld> <def>Silt; mud deposited by
water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sullage piece</b></col> <fld>(Founding)</fld>, <cd>the
sprue of a casting. See <er>Sprue</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 1
<sd>(b)</sd>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sullen</ent>⟦br⟧
